// The WebSocket session frame contract (design §00 S3, §01 G2, D4 §1.1) — the
// live duplex channel. These are the SAME protobuf message types the control
// plane is generated from, carried over WebSocket (binary protobuf) rather than
// Connect, because browser bidi needs HTTP/2 end-to-end and WS is the
// bulletproof duplex (§00 S3).
//
// Two envelopes, one per direction. Each is a oneof so a single WS message type
// carries any frame. The vocabulary is normalized + provider-agnostic (§01 G2):
// the gateway/agent emit one stable event model regardless of the provider
// behind it.
//
// D-029 RULE (TUI bullet): worker/brain state on the wire EXTENDS the
// `session_event` payload (worker_id/role/parent/status/claim/model/phase) —
// there are NO new frame types for the brain view. The brain/worker frames are
// present from S2 even though early clients render only the idle feed, so the
// expanded brain view (S4) plugs onto an existing stream (D4 §12).

